{{Short description|Japanese artist (1712–1788)}} |italic=no}}, specifically a [[:en:Miage-nyūdō|Miage-nyūdō]], as portrayed by Toriyama]] {{nihongo|'''Toriyama Sekien'''|鳥山 石燕|extra=1712 &ndash; September 22, 1788}}, real name '''Sano Toyofusa''', was a scholar, ''[[:en:Kyōka|Kyōka]]'' poet, and ''[[ukiyo-e]]'' artist of [[Japanese folklore]]. Born to a family of high-Ranking servants to the [[Tokugawa shogunate]], he was trained by [[:en:Kanō school|Kanō school]] artists Kanō Gyokuen and Kanō Chikanobu, although he was never officially recognized as a Kanō school painter.<ref>{{cite book | last = Davis | first = Julie | title = Partners in Print: Artistic Collaboration and the Ukiyo-e Market | publisher = University of Hawaii Press | year = 2015 | page = 25 | url=http://www.uhpress.hawaii.edu/p-9337-9780824839383.aspx | isbn = 978-0-8248-3938-3 }}</ref>
==Art career== After retiring from service to the shogunate, he became a teacher to numerous apprentices in poetry and painting. He was among the first to apply Kanō techniques to ''[[ukiyo-e]]'' printmaking, inventing key new techniques along the way, such as ''fuki-bokashi'', which allowed for replicating color gradations.<ref>{{cite book | last = Davis | first = Julie | title = Utamaro and the Spectacle of Beauty | publisher = University of Hawaii Press | year = 2007 | page = 33 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oZTrAAAAMAAJ&q=fuki-bokashi+sekien | isbn = 978-0-8248-3199-8 }}</ref> Most famously, he was the teacher of [[:en:Kitagawa Utamaro|Kitagawa Utamaro]] and [[Utagawa Toyoharu]].<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Yoda | first1 = Hiroko | last2 = Alt | first2 = Matt |title = Japandemonium Illustrated: The Yokai Encyclopedias of Toriyama Sekien | publisher = Dover Publications | year = 2017 | page = vii | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Hj9-rgEACAAJ | isbn = 978-0-4868-0035-6 }}</ref>
Sekien is best known for his mass-produced illustrated books of [[yōkai]] that had appeared in ''[[:en:Hyakki Yagyō|Hyakki Yagyō]]'' monster parade scrolls. The first book proved popular enough to spawn three sequels, the last of which features yōkai mainly out of Sekien's imagination. Although sometimes described as a "demonologist," his work is better described as a literary parody of encyclopedias such as the Japanese ''[[Wakan Sansai Zue]]'' or the Chinese ''[[:en:Classic of Mountains and Seas|Classic of Mountains and Seas]]'', which were popular in Japan at the time.<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Yoda | first1 = Hiroko | last2 = Alt | first2 = Matt | title = Japandemonium Illustrated: The Yokai Encyclopedias of Toriyama Sekien | publisher = Dover Publications | year = 2017 | pages = viii-ix| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Hj9-rgEACAAJ | isbn = 978-0-4868-0035-6 }}</ref> His portrayals of these creatures from folklore essentially established their visual portrayals in the public's mind and deeply inspired other Japanese artists in his own and later eras, including ukiyo-e artists [[Tsukioka Yoshitoshi]], [[:en:Kawanabe Kyōsai|Kawanabe Kyōsai]], and [[:en:Manga|Manga]] artist [[Mizuki Shigeru]].<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Yoda | first1 = Hiroko | last2 = Alt | first2 = Matt | title = Japandemonium Illustrated: The Yokai Encyclopedias of Toriyama Sekien | publisher = Dover Publications | year = 2017 | page = ix | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Hj9-rgEACAAJ | isbn = 978-0-4868-0035-6 }}</ref>
==Notable works== *{{nihongo|''[[Toriyamabiko]]''|鳥山彦|extra=published in 1773}} *{{nihongo|''[[Sekien Gafu|Sekien's Picture Album]]''|石燕画譜|extra=published in 1774}} *{{nihongo|''[[:en:Gazu Hyakki Yagyō|The Illustrated Demon Horde's Night Parade]]''|画図百鬼夜行|extra=published in 1776}} *{{nihongo|''[[:en:Konjaku Gazu Zoku Hyakki|The Illustrated Demon Horde from Past and Present, Continued]]''|今昔画図続百鬼|extra=published in 1779}} *{{nihongo|''[[:en:Konjaku Hyakki Shūi|More of the Demon Horde from Past and Present]]''|今昔百鬼拾遺|extra=published in 1780}} *Kawataro 河太郎 *Kawako 河腰 *Yamawaro 山和露 *Ushi no koku mairi 牛の国参り * * *{{nihongo|''[[:en:Gazu Hyakki Tsurezure Bukuro|A Horde of Haunted Housewares]]''|画図百鬼徒然袋|extra=published in 1784}}
==References== {{reflist}}
